14. Veneti: arugged, seafaring people, chief of the nations of Are- morica (now Brittany); they carried on trade between Gaul and Britain. The population of the region is still Celtic. It furnishes the best seamen for the F rench navy. The Veneti and their allies then controlled a com- merce extending from Ireland to Spain—Britanniam: Britain was an important Celtic country maintaining extensive commercial, social, aud political relations with the Continent.
